---
import SeoLandingLayout from "../components/SeoLandingLayout.astro";

const page = {
  title: "Makeup Photo Editor: Try a Reference Look on Your Selfie",
  description:
    "Use a makeup photo editor to preview makeup on your selfie. Choose a curated look or privately upload a reference image for AI makeup transfer.",
  heroImage: "/images/article-ai-photo-baseline.webp",
  ogImage: "/images/article-ai-photo-baseline.webp",
  heroCtaHref: "/reference-tryon?source=seo_makeup_photo_editor",
  heroCtaLabel: "Edit My Selfie with a Makeup Reference",
  faq: [
    {
      q: "Can a makeup photo editor copy a reference look?",
      a: "Reference-based AI can extract cosmetic direction such as eyeshadow, eyeliner, blush, lips, and base finish from one image and adapt it to a different selfie. It should not copy the reference person’s identity.",
    },
    {
      q: "Is this a manual makeup editor?",
      a: "No. AI Beauty Stylist is decision-focused rather than a brush-by-brush retouching tool. You choose a curated look or reference image and the AI creates a complete preview.",
    },
    {
      q: "Which photo gives the best result?",
      a: "Use a sharp, front-facing selfie in neutral light. Avoid beauty filters, heavy shadows, hands over the face, sunglasses, and very small faces in group photos.",
    },
    {
      q: "Can I share a private reference result?",
      a: "Not in the initial private-reference experience. Reference templates and their generated results are owner-only and public sharing is disabled.",
    },
  ],
};
---

<SeoLandingLayout {...page}>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <h1>Makeup Photo Editor for Real Try-On Decisions</h1>
    <p>
      Add makeup to your own photo without manually painting every feature.
      Start from a curated direction or upload a private reference when you
      already know the look you want to test.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="seo-content">
    <div class="content-section">
      <h2>Photo Editing vs. Makeup Try-On</h2>
      <p>
        Many photo editors are designed to retouch a finished image. A makeup
        decision tool has a different job: it should help you judge whether a
        palette, placement, and finish suit your face before you recreate the
        makeup in real life.
      </p>
      <div class="compare-table-scroll">
        <table class="compare-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th></th>
              <th>Reference makeup editor</th>
              <th>Generic beauty filter</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Starting point</td>
              <td>Your chosen makeup inspiration</td>
              <td>A preset overlay</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Placement</td>
              <td>Adapted to the selfie’s visible proportions</td>
              <td>Often fixed or generalized</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Identity goal</td>
              <td>Preserve the original person</td>
              <td>May retouch or reshape</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Primary use</td>
              <td>Evaluate a makeup direction</td>
              <td>Polish a social photo</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Choose the Right Two Photos</h2>
      <h3>The reference image</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          One clearly visible face with complete eye, cheek, and lip makeup.
        </li>
        <li>Neutral enough lighting to read the true makeup colors.</li>
        <li>
          No collage, heavy text, watermark across the face, or obstruction.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Your selfie</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Front-facing, sharp, and large enough to see natural skin texture.
        </li>
        <li>Neutral expression and lighting without a beauty filter.</li>
        <li>Eyes, brows, cheeks, and lips fully visible.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What the AI Is Asked to Edit</h2>
      <p>
        The editor uses the reference for cosmetic information only: base
        finish, contour, highlight, blush, brow styling, eye makeup, and lip
        design. Your selfie remains the source for identity, facial structure,
        expression, hair, clothing, framing, and background.
      </p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <p>
          If the reference has a different face shape or eye shape, a useful
          result adapts the placement instead of pasting it at the same pixel
          coordinates.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Private Template Reuse</h2>
      <p>
        Premium users can name and save up to 30 private reference templates.
        Reusing a template does not require uploading the inspiration again.
        Generating a new result uses one normal generation credit; saving or
        deleting the template does not consume a credit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-cta" slot="cta">
    <div class="seo-cta-inner">
      <h2>Turn Your Inspiration into a Private Try-On</h2>
      <p>Upload the reference, add your selfie, and judge the makeup on you.</p>
      <a href="/reference-tryon?source=seo_makeup_photo_editor" class="cta-btn">
        Open Premium Reference Try-On
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-related" slot="related">
    <div class="related-inner">
      <h3>Related tools and guides</h3>
      <ul class="related-list">
        <li><a href="/ai-makeup-generator">AI Makeup Generator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/ai-makeup-try-on">AI Makeup Try-On</a></li>
        <li><a href="/virtual-makeup-app">Virtual Makeup App</a></li>
        <li><a href="/privacy">Photo Privacy</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</SeoLandingLayout>
